#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:92
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Vaadin is a server-side AJAX web application development framework that "
"enables developers to build high-quality user interfaces with Java. It "
"provides a library of ready-to-use user interface components and a clean "
"framework for creating your own components. The focus is on ease-of-use, re-"
"usability, extensibility, and meeting the requirements of large enterprise "
"applications. Vaadin has been used in production since 2001 and it has "
"proven to be suitable for building demanding business applications."
msgstr "Vaadin on palvelinpuolella toimiva AJAX-sovelluskehys, joka mahdollistaa korkealaatuisten web-käyttöliittymien rakentamisen Javalla. Sen sisältämä kirjasto tarjoaa laajan valikoiman käyttöliittymäkomponentteja ja selkeän kehyksen omien komponenttien rakentamiseksi. Pääpaino on käytön helppoudessa, uudelleenkäytettävyydessä, laajennettavuudessa ja suurten ohjelmistojen vaatimusten täyttäminen. Vaadin on ollut tuotantokäytössä vuodesta 2001 alkaen ja on osoittautunut hyvin soveltuvaksi vaativien ohjelmistotuotteiden kehittämiseen."

#. Tag: title
#: book.xml:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preface"
msgstr "Esipuhe"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This book provides an overview of Vaadin and covers the most important "
"topics which you might encounter when developing applications with it. A "
"more detailed documentation of individual classes, interfaces, and methods "
"is given in the Java API Reference."
msgstr "Tämä kirja tarjoaa yleiskatsauksen Vaadinista ja kattaa tärkeimmät aiheet, joita Vaadinin käyttäjä saattaa kohdata kehitystyön aikana. Erillinen Java-rajanpinnan dokumentaatio sisältää tarkemmat kuvaukset yksittäisistä luokista, luokkarajapinnoista ja metodeista."

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can browse an online version of this book at the Vaadin website "
"<uri>http://vaadin.com/</uri>. A PDF version is also included in the Vaadin "
"installation package and if you install the Vaadin Plugin for Eclipse, you "
"can browse it in the Eclipse Help. You may find the HTML or the Eclipse Help "
"plugin version more easily searchable than this printed book or the PDF "
"version, but the content is the same. Just like the rest of Vaadin, this "
"book is open source."
msgstr "Voit selata tämän kirjan online-versiota Vaadinin verkkosivuilla osoitteessa <uri>http://vaadin.com/book</uri>. Vaadinin asennuspaketti sisältää myös tulostettavan PDF-version kirjasta ja jos asennat Vaadin-lisäosan Eclipseen, on kirja luettavissa Eclipsen ohjetoiminnon kautta. HTML ja Eclipsen ohjeversio ovat helpommin etsittäviä kuin painettu kirja tai PDF-versio, mutta sisältö on sama. Kuten itse Vaadin, on myös tämä kirja avointa lähdekoodia."

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Writing this manual is ongoing work and this first edition represents a "
"snapshot around the release of Vaadin 6.1. A preview edition of this book "
"was published in May 2009, just before the first release of Vaadin 6. This "
"edition contains a large number of additions and corrections related to "
"Vaadin 6. While much of the book has been reviewed by the development team, "
"it is possible if not probable that errors and outdated sections still "
"remain. Many sections are under work and will be expanded in future."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: book.xml:148
#, no-c-format
msgid "Who is This Book For?"
msgstr "Kenelle tämä kirja on tarkoitettu?"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:150
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This book is intended for software developers who use, or are considering to "
"use, Vaadin to develop web applications."
msgstr "Tämä kirja on tarkoitettu ohjelmistokehittäjille, jotka käyttävät tai harkitsevat käyttää Vaadinia web-sovellusten kehittämiseen."

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:155
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The book assumes that you have some experience with programming in Java, but "
"if not, it is as easy to begin learning Java with Vaadin as with any other "
"UI framework if not easier. No knowledge of AJAX is needed as it is well "
"hidden from the developer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:162
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You may have used some desktop-oriented user interface frameworks for Java, "
"such as AWT, Swing, or SWT. Or a library such as Qt for C++. Such knowledge "
"is useful for understanding the scope of Vaadin, the event-driven "
"programming model, and other common concepts of UI frameworks, but not "
"necessary."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you don't have a web graphics designer at hand, knowing the basics of "
"HTML and CSS can help, so that you can develop presentation themes for your "
"application. A brief introduction to CSS is provided. Knowledge of Google "
"Web Toolkit (GWT) may be useful if you develop or integrate new client-side "
"components."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: book.xml:180
#, no-c-format
msgid "Organization of This Book"
msgstr "Kirjan rakenne"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:182
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Book of Vaadin gives an introduction to what <productname>Vaadin</"
"productname> is and how you use it to develop web applications."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The chapter gives introduction to the application architecture supported by "
"Vaadin, the core design ideas behind the framework, and some historical "
"background."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:202
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter gives practical instructions for installing Vaadin and the "
"reference toolchain, including the Vaadin Plugin for Eclipse, how to run and "
"debug the demos, and how to create your own application project in the "
"Eclipse IDE."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:213
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter gives an introduction to the architecture of Vaadin and its "
"major technologies, including AJAX, Google Web Toolkit, JSON, and event-"
"driven programming."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:223
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter gives all the practical knowledge required for creating "
"applications with Vaadin, such as window management, application lifecycle, "
"deployment in a servlet container, and handling events, errors, and "
"resources."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:234
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter essentially gives the reference documentation for all the core "
"user interface components in Vaadin and their most significant features. The "
"text gives examples for using each of the components."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter describes the layout components, which are used for managing "
"the layout of the user interface, just like in any desktop application "
"frameworks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter gives instructions for using the visual editor for Eclipse, "
"which is included in the Vaadin Plugin for the Eclipse IDE."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:265
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter gives an introduction to Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) and "
"explains how you can use them to build custom visual themes for your "
"application."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter gives an overview of the built-in data model of Vaadin, "
"consisting of properties, items, and containers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:284
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter describes the process of creating new client-side widgets with "
"Google Web Toolkit (GWT) and integrating them with server-side counterparts. "
"The chapter also gives practical instructions for creating widget projects "
"in Eclipse, and using the GWT Hosted Mode Browser."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter provides many special topics that are commonly needed in "
"applications, such as opening new browser windows, embedding applications in "
"regular web pages, low-level management of resources, shortcut keys, "
"debugging, etc."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:307
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter gives an outline of the low-level UIDL messaging language, "
"normally hidden from the developer. The chapter includes the description of "
"the serialization API needed for synchronizing the component state between "
"the client-side and server-side components."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:319
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mythological background of the word Vaadin."
msgstr "Taustaa Vaadin-nimestä kansantaruissa."

#. Tag: title
#: book.xml:330
#, no-c-format
msgid "Supplementary Material"
msgstr "Lisäaineistot"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Vaadin installation package and websites offer plenty of material that "
"can help you understand what Vaadin is, what you can do with it, and how you "
"can do it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: book.xml:340
#, no-c-format
msgid "Demo Applications"
msgstr "Esimerkkisovellukset"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The installation package of Vaadin includes a number of demo applications "
"that you can run and use with your web browser. The content browser allows "
"you to view the source code of the individual demo applications. You should "
"find especially the Sampler demo a good friend of yours."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can find the demo applications online at <link xlink:href=\"http://"
"vaadin.com/\">http://vaadin.com/</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: book.xml:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "Address Book Tutorial"
msgstr "Tutoriaali: osoitekirja"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:359
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Address Book is a sample application accompanied with a tutorial that "
"gives detailed step-by-step instructions for creating a real-life web "
"application with Vaadin. You can find the tutorial from the product website."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: book.xml:368
#, no-c-format
msgid "Developer's Website"
msgstr "Kehittäjien verkkosivusto"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:370
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Vaadin Developer's Site at <link xlink:href=\"http://dev.vaadin.com/"
"\">http://dev.vaadin.com/</link> provides various online resources, such as "
"the ticket system, a development wiki, source repositories, activity "
"timeline, development milestones, and so on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:378
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The wiki provides instructions for developers, especially for those who wish "
"to check-out and compile Vaadin itself from the source repository. The "
"technical articles deal with integration of Vaadin applications with various "
"systems, such as JSP, Maven, Spring, Hibernate, and portals. The wiki also "
"provides answers to Frequently Asked Questions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: book.xml:389
#, no-c-format
msgid "Online Documentation"
msgstr "Verkosta luettavat ohjeet"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:391
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can read this book online at <link xlink:href=\"http://vaadin.com/book"
"\">http://vaadin.com/book</link>. Lots of additional material, including "
"technical HOWTOs, answers to Frequently Asked Questions and other "
"documentation is also available on <link xlink:href=\"http://dev.vaadin.com/"
"\">Vaadin web-site</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: book.xml:404
#, no-c-format
msgid "Support"
msgstr "Tuotetuki"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:406
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Stuck with a problem? No need to lose your hair over it, the Vaadin "
"developer community and the IT Mill company offer support for all of your "
"needs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: book.xml:414
#, no-c-format
msgid "Community Support Forum"
msgstr "Yhteisön tukifoorumi"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:416
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can find the user and developer community forum for Vaadin at <link "
"xlink:href=\"http://vaadin.com/forum\">http://vaadin.com/forum</link>. "
"Please use the forum to discuss any problems you might encounter, wishes for "
"features, and so on. The answer for your problems may already lie in the "
"forum archives, so searching the discussions is always the best way to begin."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: book.xml:429
#, no-c-format
msgid "Report Bugs"
msgstr "Ilmoita virheistä"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:431
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have found a possible bug in Vaadin, the demo applications, or the "
"documentation, please report it by filing a ticket at the Vaadin developer's "
"site at <link xlink:href=\"http://dev.vaadin.com/\">http://dev.vaadin.com/</"
"link>. You may want to check the existing tickets before filing a new one. "
"You can make a ticket to make a request for a new feature as well, or to "
"suggest modifications to an existing feature."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: book.xml:445
#, no-c-format
msgid "Commercial Support"
msgstr "Kaupallinen tuotetuki"

#. Tag: para
#: book.xml:447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"IT Mill offers full commercial support and training services for the Vaadin "
"products. Read more about the commercial products at <link xlink:href="
"\"http://vaadin.com/pro\">http://vaadin.com/pro</link> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
